<class module="platform" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.platform.BPlatformService" name="BPlatformService" packageName="com.tridium.platform" public="true" abstract="true">
<description>
A platform service is the interface for a service, device, or protocol which&#xa; is managed by the platform OS (using an API, config files, etc.), native&#xa; or third-party software.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; It may provide a management interface or simply provide read-only access to&#xa; configuration properties.&#xa; &lt;p&gt;&#xa; Since most platform service properties are managed outside of Niagara, and&#xa; their values are persisted using native methods or config files, the&#xa; properties should have their transient attributes set so that they&#xa; are not also saved to the platform.bog file.
</description>
